In [[theatre studies]], '''didaskalia''' is anything written within a [[play (theatre)|play]] text that is not directly spoken by a [[character (arts)|character]].  The term is the modern re-use of the theatrical term of the [[classical antiquity]] [[wikt:διδασκαλία|διδασκαλία]] literally meaning "teaching", "instruction".<ref>The Cambridge Introduction to Theatre Studies</ref><ref>[http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803095717703]</ref><ref>[http://www.encyklopediateatru.pl/hasla/212/didaskalia]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=J88fLaFswBAC&pg=PA25]</ref><ref>[http://www.literaryterminology.com/index.php/lemmas/11-d/297-didaskalia]</ref>

