{{ref improve|date=March 2017}} {{Infobox magazine |image_file = |image_size = |image_caption = |editor = |editor_title = |frequency = Monthly |total_circulation = |circulation_year = |category =[[Motion-picture industry]] |company = |country = United States <!--[[WP:ICONDECORATION]]--> |publisher = [[Prometheus Global Media|Mediabistro Holdings]] |founded = 1934 |finaldate = |based =New York City |language =English |website = {{URL|http://filmjournal.com}} |issn = 1526-9884 }} '''''Film Journal International''''' is a [[motion-picture industry]] [[trade magazine]] published by the [[United States|American]] company [[Prometheus Global Media]].<ref name=cp/> It is a sister publication of ''[[Adweek]]'', ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', and other periodicals.<ref name=cp>{{cite book|author1=Clyde Philip Rolston|author2=Amy Macy|author3=Tom Hutchison|author4=Paul Allen|title=Record Label Marketing: How Music Companies Brand and Market Artists in the Digital Era|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tm74CgAAQBAJ&pg=PT453|accessdate=March 4, 2017|date=November 19, 2015|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-1-134-70555-9|page=453}}</ref>
==History and profile== Launched in 1934 and published monthly, ''Film Journal International'' covers exhibition, production, and distribution, reporting both U.S. and international news, with features on industry trends, [[movie theater]] design and technology, screen [[advertising]], and other topics. It is the official magazine of the industry conventions [[ShoWest]], ShowEast, [[Cinema Expo International]], and CineAsia.
In 2008, it was based at 770 [[Broadway (Manhattan)|Broadway]], [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]]. The editor and publisher is Robert Sunshine, and the executive editor is Kevin Lally. Its [[film critic]]s include Lewis Beale, [[Frank Lovece]], [[Maitland McDonagh]], Rebecca Pahle, David Noh, and Doris Toumarkine. Rex Roberts is the associate editor and graphic designer, and as of at last 2016, Sarah Sluis is the assistant editor/staff writer, a post previously held by Katey Rich.
