{{Orphan|date=June 2015}}
'''Hot Tub Cinema''' is a [[film|cinematic]] experience created in 2012.<ref name=goingout>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/goingout/film/lovely-bubbly-take-a-dip-at-the-hot-tub-cinema-7917652.html|title=Lovely bubbly: take a dip at the Hot Tub Cinema|work=The Evening Standard}}</ref>
==Overview== Created by Asher Charman,<ref name=goingout/> the events combine popular films with [[hot tub]]s, often in unusual spaces such as rooftops, old factories or abandoned train stations (such as the former [[Shoreditch tube station|Shoreditch Underground Station]] in [[Shoreditch]], [[London]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://now-here-this.timeout.com/2014/05/27/hot-tub-cinema-goes-underground/|title=Hot Tub Cinema goes underground|work=Time Out Blog}}</ref> In addition to watching a film, cinema-goers have the opportunity to celebrate after the film with a [[VJing|VJ]]-led party.
In addition to shows in London, Hot Tub Cinema events have been held in [[New York City]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2014/05/09/hot-tub-cinema-series-makes-a-splash-in-brooklyn/|title=Hot Tub Cinema series makes a splash in Brooklyn|work=New York Post}}</ref> [[Ibiza]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibiza-spotlight.com/night/2014/09/news-hot-tub-cinema-party-ibiza-rocks|title=NEWS - Hot Tub Cinema Party at Ibiza Rocks|work=Ibiza Spotlight}}</ref> and in several cities around the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bristolpost.co.uk/Prepare-sequel-Hot-tub-cinema-coming-Bristol/story-26127026-detail/story.html|title=Prepare for the sequel: Hot tub cinema is coming back to Bristol|work=Bristol Post}}</ref>
==Notable screenings== In addition to regular shows, Hot Tub Cinema has also been involved in several film & TV launches, such as a one-off launch screening [[Spring Breakers]] which included an appearance from the writer/director [[Harmony Korine]]. Held in an abandoned fire station in South London, in addition to the film and afterparty guests could experience recreations of iconic scenes throughout the venue.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LEi692I_14g</ref>
They also created an event for a DVD launch of ''[[The Walking Dead (TV series)|The Walking Dead]]'', which included (real) roast squirrel and a tub full of blood and limbs.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.582125798510345.1073741826.161577853898477&type=3</ref>
