{{Infobox video game |title = Kung-Fu Live |image = [[File:PSblog kungfulive.jpg|frameless|upright=1.15]] |caption = Kung-Fu Live logo |developer = Virtual Air Guitar |publisher = Virtual Air Guitar |designer = |engine = |released = {{vgrelease|NA|7 December 2010<ref name="release">http://uk.gamespot.com/ps3/action/kungfulive/similar.html?mode=versions</ref>}}{{vgrelease|EU|8 December 2010<ref name="release"/>}}{{vgrelease|AUS|8 December 2010<ref name="release"/>}} |genre = [[Action game|Action]], [[Fighting game|Fighting]] |modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-Player]], [[Multiplayer video game|Multiplayer]] |platforms = [[PlayStation 3]] ([[PlayStation Network]]) }}
'''Kung-Fu Live''' is an interactive [[fighting game]] developed by Virtual Air Guitar Company exclusively for the [[PlayStation Network]].<ref>http://blog.us.playstation.com/2010/05/26/kung-fu-live-for-ps3-you-are-the-controller/</ref>
The game tracks the players movement using the [[PlayStation Eye]] and free-motion technology.<ref>http://www.kungfulivegame.com/press/newyork</ref>
It is quoted as being the best of the PlayStation 3 Fitness Games, "I would say it is a must-have if you’re a fan of fighting games and want to see what the future holds for innovative, creative game design,"<ref>http://www.ps3fitness.com/</ref>
==Reception== {{Video game reviews | GR = 53.76%<ref name=GR>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerankings.com/ps3/996587-kung-fu-live/index.html|title=Kung-Fu Live|publisher=[[GameRankings]]|accessdate=14 January 2012}}</ref> | MC = 50/100<ref name=MC>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/kung-fu-live|title=Kung-Fu Live|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=14 January 2012}}</ref> }}
''Kung-Fu Live'' has received generally mixed reviews. It had an average score of 53.76% at [[GameRankings]], based on 27 reviews<ref name=GR/> and an average score of 50/100 at [[Metacritic]], based on 30 reviews.<ref name=MC/>
Ryan Clements, a writer for [[IGN]] who rated the game a 40/100, wrote that the game "has an appealing premise and fun visuals, but I can't recommend a game that left me feeling so defeated."<ref name=IGN>{{cite web|url=http://ps3.ign.com/articles/113/1139562p1.html|title=Kung-Fu Live Review|publisher=[[IGN]]|accessdate=14 January 2012}}</ref>
Steven Williamson, who writes for [[PSU.com]] and rated the game a 5.5/10, says "Meet the strict criteria for set-up and calibration and you might enjoy the novelty of seeing yourself kicking ass on screen, but you'll still have to battle with the controls just as much as you will against the bad guys."<ref name=PSU.com>{{cite web|url=http://www.psu.com/Kung-Fu-Live-Review--a010307-p0.php|title=Kung-Fu Live Review|publisher=[[PSU.com]]|accessdate=14 January 2012}}</ref>
